#include "story_data.h"
const orca_story_t g_orca_stories[] = {
  {"A dolphin at the top","Orcas are toothed whales and the largest members of the oceanic dolphin family. Their size and familiar black-and-white pattern make them unmistakable.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=A%20dolphin%20at%20the%20top%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"One living Orcinus","The orca is the only living species currently recognized in the genus Orcinus, although scientists continue to study whether some ecotypes may be distinct species or subspecies.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=One%20living%20Orcinus%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"At home in every ocean","Orcas have a cosmopolitan range: they occur in every ocean and in most seas. They are especially common in productive, cooler coastal waters.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=At%20home%20in%20every%20ocean%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Built on a huge scale","Adult males are typically 6 to 8 meters long and can exceed 6 metric tons. Females are generally 5 to 7 meters long and weigh about 3 to 4 tons.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Built%20on%20a%20huge%20scale%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"A 400-pound newborn","A newborn calf is roughly 2.4 meters long and weighs about 180 kilograms, entering the water already larger than many adult humans.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=A%20400-pound%20newborn%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"A six-foot dorsal fin","The tall, straight dorsal fin of an adult male can reach about 1.8 meters. Female and juvenile fins are shorter and more curved.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=A%20six-foot%20dorsal%20fin%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"The eye patch is not the eye","An orca's actual eye is small and sits below and forward of the large white eye patch. A gray or white saddle patch lies behind the dorsal fin.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=The%20eye%20patch%20is%20not%20the%20eye%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Calves wear orange","The pale areas of newborn orcas can look yellow or orange rather than bright white. Their coloring changes as they mature.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Calves%20wear%20orange%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Photo-ID fingerprints","Researchers identify individuals from the shape, scars, and nicks of the dorsal fin plus the pattern of the saddle patch. Long-running photo catalogs reveal family histories.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Photo-ID%20fingerprints%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Seeing with sound","Orcas use echolocation clicks to investigate their surroundings and locate prey. They listen for echoes that reveal an object's position and features.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Seeing%20with%20sound%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Wrapped in blubber","A thick blubber layer, commonly about 7.6 to 10 centimeters, insulates an orca and stores energy in cold ocean water.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Wrapped%20in%20blubber%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"The diving heart","An orca's pulse is about 60 beats per minute at the surface and can slow to roughly 30 while submerged, helping conserve oxygen during a dive.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=The%20diving%20heart%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Apex but specialized","Orcas are apex predators, yet different populations specialize in very different prey, including fish, sharks, rays, seals, dolphins, and large whales.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Apex%20but%20specialized%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Families led by mothers","Many orcas live in stable matrilineal groups built around an older female and her descendants. Sons and daughters may remain closely bonded to their mothers for life.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Families%20led%20by%20mothers%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Culture beneath the waves","Hunting techniques, food preferences, and call repertoires are learned socially and passed between generations. Distinct communities can have traditions of their own.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Culture%20beneath%20the%20waves%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Different ways to be an orca","Resident, Bigg's, and offshore orcas in the North Pacific differ in diet, movement, social life, appearance, and calls. Scientists call such distinct forms ecotypes.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Different%20ways%20to%20be%20an%20orca%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Why 'killer whale'?","The old name came from sailors who watched orcas hunting larger whales and called them whale killers. Over time, the words were reversed to killer whale.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Why%20'killer%20whale'%3F%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Wild encounters are rarely dangerous","No fatal attack on a human by a wild orca has been documented. Captive orcas, however, have injured people and have been involved in human deaths.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Wild%20encounters%20are%20rarely%20dangerous%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Visitors to freshwater","Orcas sometimes enter bays, estuaries, and rivers. They have been recorded about 160 kilometers up the Columbia River in pursuit of fish.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Visitors%20to%20freshwater%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Global range, local danger","The species is globally listed as Data Deficient by the IUCN, while some local populations are endangered. Threats include prey loss, pollution, noise, captures, and conflict with fisheries.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orca","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Global%20range%2C%20local%20danger%20orca%20fact",0},
  {"Shamu","The original Shamu was a young female Southern Resident captured in 1965. After her death, SeaWorld reused her name as a stage identity for many different orcas.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shamu","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Shamu%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Namu","Namu was accidentally caught near British Columbia in 1965 and became one of the first captive orcas to gain international fame. His story helped launch the marine-park orca era.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Namu_(orca)","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Namu%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Moby Doll","Moby Doll was harpooned off British Columbia in 1964 for use as a model, but survived for months in captivity. His gentle behavior contradicted the era's image of orcas as monsters.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moby_Doll","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Moby%20Doll%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Tokitae","Also called Lolita and Sk'aliCh'elh-tenaut, Tokitae was taken from L Pod at Penn Cove in 1970. Plans to return her to a seaside sanctuary were unfinished when she died in 2023.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lolita_(orca)","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Tokitae%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Corky II","Captured from the Northern Resident A5 family in 1969, Corky became the longest-held captive orca. OrcaLab continues to advocate for an ocean sanctuary in her home waters.","https://orcalab.org/free-corky/","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Corky%20II%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Orky II","Orky II was captured in 1968 and paired with Corky. He helped lift Corky's first live-born calf to the surface and later fathered Orkid before dying in 1988.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_captive_orcas","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Orky%20II%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Kandu V","Kandu V was captured near Iceland. In 1989 she charged Corky during a show, fractured her own jaw, and died?an event that exposed the dangers of forced social groupings.","https://orcalab.org/free-corky/","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Kandu%20V%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Kalina","Born in 1985, Kalina was promoted as the first captive-born orca to survive infancy. Her life marked the shift from wild capture toward captive breeding.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_captive_orcas","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Kalina%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Kasatka","Kasatka was captured near Iceland in 1978 and became a dominant matriarch at SeaWorld San Diego. She was euthanized in 2017 after chronic lung disease.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_captive_orcas","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Kasatka%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Orkid","Orkid was born to Kandu V and Orky II in 1988. After her mother?s death, Corky acted as her surrogate, creating one of captivity?s most unusual social bonds.","https://orcalab.org/free-corky/","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Orkid%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Kiska","Captured near Iceland in 1979, Kiska outlived all five of her calves. After her final tank-mate left, she spent years alone and became known as ?the loneliest orca.?","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_captive_orcas","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Kiska%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Morgan","Morgan was found emaciated in Dutch waters in 2010. Though rehabilitated, she was transferred to Loro Parque rather than released, prompting an enduring legal and scientific dispute.","https://whales.org/action/orca-morgan/","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Morgan%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Wikie","Born in France, Wikie became widely known through research showing she could copy novel sounds?including rough imitations of human words?on command.","https://royalsocietypublishing.org/doi/10.1098/rspb.2017.2171","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Wikie%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Keto","Keto was born at SeaWorld Orlando and transferred repeatedly before living at Loro Parque. In 2009 he was involved in trainer Alexis Mart?nez?s death.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_captive_orcas","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Keto%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Hugo","Hugo was captured in Puget Sound in 1968 and later shared a small stadium pool with Tokitae. He died in 1980 after years of captivity at Miami Seaquarium.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_captive_orcas","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Hugo%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Chimo","Chimo was a pale, nearly white young orca displayed in Victoria. Her coloring was linked to Chediak-Higashi syndrome; she died after only a few years in captivity.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chimo_(orca)","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Chimo%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Jumbo","Jumbo was a young Southern Resident taken in the 1970 Penn Cove capture. Sent to Kamogawa Sea World with Chappy, he died from liver dysfunction in 1974.","https://www.keikoconservation.org/blog/japanese-dolphinariums-101-kamogawa-seaworld","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Jumbo%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Springer A73","Found alone and underweight near Seattle, Springer was treated, transported north, and reunited with her Northern Resident relatives in 2002. She later raised calves of her own.","https://orcalab.org/springers-story/","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Springer%20A73%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Luna L98","Separated from L Pod, Luna sought contact with boats and people in Nootka Sound. Competing rescue plans failed, and he was killed by a tugboat propeller in 2006.","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luna_(orca)","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Luna%20L98%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Granny J2","Granny was the best-known elder of J Pod and often traveled at its head. Her exact age was debated, but her leadership made her a symbol of Southern Resident culture.","https://www.whalemuseum.org/collections/meet-the-whales","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Granny%20J2%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Ruffles J1","Ruffles was instantly recognizable by his tall, rippled dorsal fin. The adult male frequently traveled with Granny and became an icon of the Salish Sea.","https://www.whalemuseum.org/collections/meet-the-whales","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Ruffles%20J1%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Tahlequah J35","After her calf died in 2018, Tahlequah carried the body for 17 days and roughly 1,000 miles. Her visible mourning drew worldwide attention to Southern Resident losses.","https://whalemuseum.org/products/orcasharedwaterssharedhome","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Tahlequah%20J35%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Ocean Sun L25","Ocean Sun is the oldest known Southern Resident and may be Tokitae?s mother. She is the last surviving member known from the population?s capture era.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Ocean%20Sun%20L25%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Slick J16","Slick is one of J Pod?s most successful mothers. In her forties she gave birth to Scarlet?well beyond the usual reproductive age expected for the population.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Slick%20J16%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Mike J26","Mike was named for scientist Michael Bigg, whose photo-identification methods revealed orca families and lifespans without capturing them.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Mike%20J26%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Port & Starboard","Off South Africa, these two adult males became famous for hunting sharks and selectively removing energy-rich livers. In 2023, Starboard killed a juvenile great white alone and removed its liver in under two minutes. This is a learned specialization, not a habit of every orca population.","https://www.nhm.ac.uk/discover/news/2024/march/solo-south-african-orcas-learn-how-hunt-great-white-sharks.html","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Port%20Starboard%20orcas%20great%20white%20shark%20liver",1},
  {"Echo J42","Echo is Slick?s youngest surviving offspring. Genetic analysis showed her father was her older brother Mike, illustrating the population?s severe inbreeding risk.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Echo%20J42%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Scarlet J50","Scarlet survived a difficult birth and became beloved for her playful breaches. In 2018, researchers attempted an unprecedented feeding and treatment response before she disappeared.","https://whalemuseum.org/collections/meet-the-whales","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Scarlet%20J50%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Phoenix J57","Born two years after Tahlequah?s famous tour of grief, Phoenix survived and thrived. His name was chosen to symbolize life rising after profound loss.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Phoenix%20J57%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Shachi J19","Once known for babysitting other calves, Shachi became a mother and grandmother. After Granny?s death, observers increasingly saw her directing J Pod?s movements.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Shachi%20J19%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Eclipse J41","Eclipse is Shachi?s daughter and mother to Nova and Crescent. Their close association makes the J19 family a visible three-generation matriline.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Eclipse%20J41%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Nova J51","Nova was born during the 2015 Southern Resident baby boom. Genetic work identified his father as L41 Mega, an older L Pod male.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Nova%20J51%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Oreo J22","Oreo anchors the J22 matriline. After losing her son DoubleStuf, her surviving family consists of her adult son Cookie.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Oreo%20J22%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Iceberg CO539","Researchers first photographed Iceberg near Russia's Commander Islands in 2010. His two-metre dorsal fin showed he was a mature male, and he appeared healthy within his pod. Although often called albino, photographs alone did not confirm true albinism; some pigmentation may remain.","https://russianorca.com/index.php?lang=en","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Iceberg%20CO539%20white%20orca%20Russian%20Far%20East",1},
  {"Spock K20","Spock?s fin once led researchers to think she was male. The birth of her calf Comet proved otherwise; decades later she produced Prosper, a rare K Pod calf.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Spock%20K20%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Comet K38","Comet?s 2004 birth revealed that his sprouting-fin mother Spock was female. Genetic analysis later identified L41 Mega as his father.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Comet%20K38%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Prosper K45","Prosper?s arrival in 2022 was K Pod?s first successful birth in more than a decade. Researchers later confirmed that the calf was female.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Prosper%20K45%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Onyx L87","After losing his close maternal relatives, Onyx began traveling with J Pod instead of his native L Pod?an unusual change in a society built around lifelong family bonds.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Onyx%20L87%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Mega L41","Mega was a large L Pod male. Genetic studies identified him as the father of calves in multiple pods, including Echo?s generation, before his disappearance.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Mega%20L41%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Rhapsody J32","When Rhapsody died in 2014, examination showed she had been carrying a near-term female fetus. The double loss intensified concern about pregnancy failure and food limitation.","https://www.damtruth.org/j32-rhapsody","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Rhapsody%20J32%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Mystery L85","Mystery once approached a research vessel and repeatedly produced an L Pod contact call. The encounter offered a vivid glimpse of orca social curiosity.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/meet-the-southern-residents","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Mystery%20L85%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Indy T65A5","Indy became famous for traveling independently at an unusually young age. His mammal-eating Bigg?s family has helped reveal rapid cultural and population changes.","https://www.orcaconservancy.org/transient-killer-whales","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Indy%20T65A5%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Wake T46","Wake was among six young orcas corralled in Budd Inlet in 1976. All escaped or were released; her descendants now form a large, well-known Bigg?s lineage.","https://www.orcabehaviorinstitute.org/orca-updates/the-budd-inlet-six-whales","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Wake%20T46%20orca%20whale%20story",1},
  {"Kesha's psychedelic orca","Kesha revealed a neon pink-and-yellow-green orca tattoo on her forearm in January 2017. It joined her growing collection of colorful sea-creature tattoos, including a humpback whale, whale shark, and narwhal.","https://www.teenvogue.com/story/kesha-orca-whale-tattoo","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Kesha+orca+whale+tattoo",2},
  {"Jambu / Willzyx","Jambu is not a real individual. He is the captive orca in South Park's Free Willzyx, a dark parody of marine-park shows and Free Willy-style rescue stories.","https://southpark.cc.com/video-clips/3b5lpu/south-park-jambu-speaks","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=South%20Park%20Jambu%20Free%20Willzyx",2},
  {"Free Willy / Keiko","Keiko played Willy in the 1993 film Free Willy, a fantasy of instant liberation. His real rehabilitation took years, cost millions, and ended with a return to the North Atlantic - but not a lasting reunion with a wild pod.","https://www.oregonencyclopedia.org/articles/keiko/","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Free%20Willy%20%2F%20Keiko%20orca%20whale%20story",3},
  {"Blackfish / Tilikum","The 2013 documentary Blackfish built its captivity critique around Tilikum and trainer Dawn Brancheau's death. SeaWorld disputed the film, but its enormous reach reshaped public opinion and intensified pressure on marine parks.","https://time.com/4625924/seaworld-killer-whale-tilikum-dies/","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Blackfish%20%2F%20Tilikum%20orca%20whale%20story",3},
  {"Rory and the Northern Lights","In Rory: An Orca's Quest for the Northern Lights, a young orca follows his dream north and finds friendship along the way. Sarah Cullen and Carmen Ellis's rhyming picture book mixes an ocean adventure with perseverance, teamwork, and animal facts.","https://mitpressbookstore.mit.edu/book/9780648849872","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Rory%20An%20Orca%20Quest%20for%20the%20Northern%20Lights%20book",3},
  {"Orca: The Whale Called Killer","Erich Hoyt blends encounters with wild British Columbia orcas, individual family stories, behavior, and natural history. First published in the early 1980s and repeatedly expanded, the book helped readers see orcas as complex social animals rather than mythical killers.","https://erichhoyt.com/books/orca-the-whale-called-killer/","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Erich%20Hoyt%20Orca%20The%20Whale%20Called%20Killer",3},
  {"Orca - Quint's boat","In Jaws, Quint, Brody, and Hooper hunt the shark aboard Orca. The hero boat began as a lobster boat named Warlock; Orca II was built to sink. Two years later, the film Orca answered Jaws with a killer-whale revenge story.","https://www.jawsmovie.com/archive/orca-boat-history.html","https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Jaws%20Orca%20boat%20behind%20the%20scenes",3},
  {"Why Orcas Refuse to Kill Us","This video essay investigates a remarkable contrast: orcas are powerful apex predators capable of hunting whales and great white sharks, yet fatal attacks on humans in the wild have not been documented.","https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VtrcKTkhDHU","https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VtrcKTkhDHU",3},
  {"Support whale research","Help keep the story alive. Scan the source QR code to support the Center for Whale Research and its long-running study of Southern Resident orcas.","https://www.whaleresearch.com/donate","https://www.whaleresearch.com/donate",3},
};
